# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarArc | Scene: WarCouncil
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "The court began its preparations as soon as the winter grace festival had ended. Only a week later, the council met."
    new "The court began its preparations as soon as the winter grace festival had ended. Only a week later, the council met."

    old "But a lot had changed in those few days."
    new "But a lot had changed in those few days."

    old "Sarah watched Thomas."
    new "Sarah watched Thomas."

    old "He sat upright, appeared more attentive, but his face had turned even more gaunt, as if he never slept at all."
    new "He sat upright, appeared more attentive, but his face had turned even more gaunt, as if he never slept at all."

    old "Sarah had not spoken to Thomas about what had happened with the emissary."
    new "Sarah had not spoken to Thomas about what had happened with the emissary."

    old "She feared that it might trouble her brother, and feared even more that it might not trouble him at all."
    new "She feared that it might trouble her brother, and feared even more that it might not trouble him at all."

    old "The emissary had been sent on his way, but every member of the council knew that his threat had not been empty."
    new "The emissary had been sent on his way, but every member of the council knew that his threat had not been empty."

    old "General Barion had finished discussing the preparations that had been made towards further mobilizing the army."
    new "General Barion had finished discussing the preparations that had been made towards further mobilizing the army."

    old "Kravel instantly followed up by reading out the most recent reports."
    new "Kravel instantly followed up by reading out the most recent reports."

    old "Every day was like this now, an endless deluge of reports from Kravel's spy network, and each seemed to paint a more disturbing picture than the last."
    new "Every day was like this now, an endless deluge of reports from Kravel's spy network, and each seemed to paint a more disturbing picture than the last."

    old "The earliest reports showed Hassar's armies moving into the eastern districts. We've still not received any confirmation on whether they actually did, nor the size of his army."
    new "The earliest reports showed Hassar's armies moving into the eastern districts. We've still not received any confirmation on whether they actually did, nor the size of his army."

    old "Marion slammed the table."
    new "Marion slammed the table."

    old "We're being taken for fools here. Yes, there is no definitive report, but that's because nobody is coming back from the eastern districts."
    new "We're being taken for fools here. Yes, there is no definitive report, but that's because nobody is coming back from the eastern districts."

    old "The Deepstill family are close friends of mine. They made their money out of mines that they own there."
    new "The Deepstill family are close friends of mine. They made their money out of mines that they own there."

    old "They haven't received a shipment since these reports started. They tell me that this has never happened before."
    new "They haven't received a shipment since these reports started. They tell me that this has never happened before."

    old "Every man they send to investigate, never reports back. The only one that did, only came back because he turned around when he saw the smoke stacks, rising over the east."
    new "Every man they send to investigate, never reports back. The only one that did, only came back because he turned around when he saw the smoke stacks, rising over the east."

    old "Enough to block out the sun, he said."
    new "Enough to block out the sun, he said."

    old "Marion fell back into his chair."
    new "Marion fell back into his chair."

    old "Look, I know there is no definitive report, but everything is telling us that the attack is real. That Hassar's army is already in the eastern district."
    new "Look, I know there is no definitive report, but everything is telling us that the attack is real. That Hassar's army is already in the eastern district."

    old "Varga spoke up this time."
    new "Varga spoke up this time."

    old "I agree with Marion. The signs are clear."
    new "I agree with Marion. The signs are clear."

    old "Also, if it is true, we need to be aware that our position is vulnerable."
    new "Also, if it is true, we need to be aware that our position is vulnerable."

    old "The eastern districts are far, but that's for a regular army."
    new "The eastern districts are far, but that's for a regular army."

    old "The eastern tribes are famous for their horses. In their army, every man has a horse, most have multiple."
    new "The eastern tribes are famous for their horses. In their army, every man has a horse, most have multiple."

    old "They can cross the distance between the eastern district and the capital much faster than a regular army could. They could cut off the capital in a matter of days."
    new "They can cross the distance between the eastern district and the capital much faster than a regular army could. They could cut off the capital in a matter of days."

    old "Marion nodded excessively."
    new "Marion nodded excessively."

    old "Thomas rubbed his temples."
    new "Thomas rubbed his temples."

    old "How could this have happened? An army, right on our doorstep, and nobody saw it coming?"
    new "How could this have happened? An army, right on our doorstep, and nobody saw it coming?"

    old "When nobody had an answer, Kravel spoke up."
    new "When nobody had an answer, Kravel spoke up."

    old "My lord, the eastern desert has always been difficult to spy on. The territory is enormous, and the people there, they aren't as easily convinced by a bribe."
    new "My lord, the eastern desert has always been difficult to spy on. The territory is enormous, and the people there, they aren't as easily convinced by a bribe."

    old "We never had to worry as much, because at most it was the occasional raid from a single tribe desperate enough to risk an attack."
    new "We never had to worry as much, because at most it was the occasional raid from a single tribe desperate enough to risk an attack."

    old "This...we've never had to deal with something like this before. I can predict what is predictable, but this is outside of anything we've ever seen."
    new "This...we've never had to deal with something like this before. I can predict what is predictable, but this is outside of anything we've ever seen."

    old "Sarah watched as Thomas slammed his fist on the table this time."
    new "Sarah watched as Thomas slammed his fist on the table this time."

    old "I don't need a spy master who can tell me all the things he doesn't know. I need you to tell me what I need to know. We don't even know for certain where this army is."
    new "I don't need a spy master who can tell me all the things he doesn't know. I need you to tell me what I need to know. We don't even know for certain where this army is."

    old "Sarah decided to interject."
    new "Sarah decided to interject."

    old "Do we have an estimate of the size of Hassar's army?"
    new "Do we have an estimate of the size of Hassar's army?"

    old "We have no report that even guesses at his army, but we know that it has to be quite large."
    new "We have no report that even guesses at his army, but we know that it has to be quite large."

    old "Well, the defense of the eastern district falls on fort Fallowhill. It's a large fortress, with a sizeable army. Large enough to defeat anything we've seen before."
    new "Well, the defense of the eastern district falls on fort Fallowhill. It's a large fortress, with a sizeable army. Large enough to defeat anything we've seen before."

    old "To be entirely accurate, it's primary purpose is to maintain order over the people of the eastern district, keep them from revolting."
    new "To be entirely accurate, it's primary purpose is to maintain order over the people of the eastern district, keep them from revolting."

    old "To that end, they're well provisioned and larger than otherwise necessary. And yet..."
    new "To that end, they're well provisioned and larger than otherwise necessary. And yet..."

    old "Yes?"
    new "Yes?"

    old "We heard nothing from them. The reports from the fort dried up a week ago."
    new "We heard nothing from them. The reports from the fort dried up a week ago."

    old "We have to assume that they have been routed, or have been forced to withdraw within the fortress walls."
    new "We have to assume that they have been routed, or have been forced to withdraw within the fortress walls."

    old "Either way, that means Hassar's army is either large enough to route our forces in the eastern district, or large enough that our forces won't even engage."
    new "Either way, that means Hassar's army is either large enough to route our forces in the eastern district, or large enough that our forces won't even engage."

    old "One way or the other, it hints at a large army."
    new "One way or the other, it hints at a large army."

    old "Sarah followed Kravel's logic, and considered it sound."
    new "Sarah followed Kravel's logic, and considered it sound."

    old "She stared off into the distance."
    new "She stared off into the distance."

    old "How did everything turn around against them, so fast..."
    new "How did everything turn around against them, so fast..."

    old "So, what can we do then? Sit here and wait for Hassar to trap us in the capital? What options do we have?"
    new "So, what can we do then? Sit here and wait for Hassar to trap us in the capital? What options do we have?"

    old "Varga cleared his throat."
    new "Varga cleared his throat."

    old "There isn't much time, and so our options are limited, having said that, there is a choice that is left to us..."
    new "There isn't much time, and so our options are limited, having said that, there is a choice that is left to us..."

    old "Say it."
    new "Say it."

    old "Varga seemed wounded by Thomas' sharp tone, but Sarah nodded at him, urging Varga to go on."
    new "Varga seemed wounded by Thomas' sharp tone, but Sarah nodded at him, urging Varga to go on."

    old "The outer districts have regional troops and militia reserves. If we call on them now, they might reach the capital in time to aid in the defense. Consolidate our forces."
    new "The outer districts have regional troops and militia reserves. If we call on them now, they might reach the capital in time to aid in the defense. Consolidate our forces."

    old "Marion sat up as if struck by lightning."
    new "Marion sat up as if struck by lightning."

    old "You're talking about the forces that guard the noble families of every district in the country."
    new "You're talking about the forces that guard the noble families of every district in the country."

    old "You're talking about drafting every man that can hold a sword and dragging them here."
    new "You're talking about drafting every man that can hold a sword and dragging them here."

    old "Varga nodded."
    new "Varga nodded."

    old "That means leaving everyone except the capital, defenseless. If Hassar avoids the capital, and attacks another district, they'll only have women and children to defend themselves."
    new "That means leaving everyone except the capital, defenseless. If Hassar avoids the capital, and attacks another district, they'll only have women and children to defend themselves."

    old "They'll be left to the slaughter!"
    new "They'll be left to the slaughter!"

    old "Perhaps, but I believe that Hassar will move on the capital. He's a tribesman, he doesn't want to fight the kinds of wars that we fight."
    new "Perhaps, but I believe that Hassar will move on the capital. He's a tribesman, he doesn't want to fight the kinds of wars that we fight."

    old "He is moving so fast, his logistics are probably weak. He will want to finish this war as fast as he can, which means going for the capital, decapitating the country."
    new "He is moving so fast, his logistics are probably weak. He will want to finish this war as fast as he can, which means going for the capital, decapitating the country."

    old "Marion turned to Thomas now, pleading for his support instead of convincing Varga."
    new "Marion turned to Thomas now, pleading for his support instead of convincing Varga."

    old "A lot has been asked of the nobility, and a lot we have given, but Thomas...my king...you will be asking them to leave their homes unguarded."
    new "A lot has been asked of the nobility, and a lot we have given, but Thomas...my king...you will be asking them to leave their homes unguarded."

    old "They will forever remember that you sacrificed their safety, to guarantee your own."
    new "They will forever remember that you sacrificed their safety, to guarantee your own."

    old "Varga also turned himself to Thomas."
    new "Varga also turned himself to Thomas."

    old "There will be no country left to defend in the capital falls. Making our stand here, means pushing Hassar's forces back into the desert. That will help everyone."
    new "There will be no country left to defend in the capital falls. Making our stand here, means pushing Hassar's forces back into the desert. That will help everyone."

    old "Marion turned himself to Varga."
    new "Marion turned himself to Varga."

    old "Absurd! You're just a nobody from some backwater, who is now trying to lure the enemy army into our capital, because you despise us."
    new "Absurd! You're just a nobody from some backwater, who is now trying to lure the enemy army into our capital, because you despise us."

    old "Marion spat in Varga's direction."
    new "Marion spat in Varga's direction."

    old "Varga's face was full of rage, but he contained himself, bearing the insult."
    new "Varga's face was full of rage, but he contained himself, bearing the insult."

    old "Sarah grabbed Thomas' arm, and whispered to him."
    new "Sarah grabbed Thomas' arm, and whispered to him."

    old "We need to make a decision, and fast, before these two start fighting."
    new "We need to make a decision, and fast, before these two start fighting."

    old "The capital must not fall; call in the troops."
    new "The capital must not fall; call in the troops."

    old "Thomas slammed the table."
    new "Thomas slammed the table."

    old "Enough, I've made up my mind."
    new "Enough, I've made up my mind."

    old "If the capital falls, the war is lost. We cannot allow this to happen."
    new "If the capital falls, the war is lost. We cannot allow this to happen."

    old "Call in all possible district troops and militia reserves, and gather everyone to the capital."
    new "Call in all possible district troops and militia reserves, and gather everyone to the capital."

    old "We will break Hassar's army on our mighty walls."
    new "We will break Hassar's army on our mighty walls."

    old "Marion's eyes spat fire, but he said nothing."
    new "Marion's eyes spat fire, but he said nothing."

    old "His quiet rage almost seemed to worry Sarah more than his overt anger."
    new "His quiet rage almost seemed to worry Sarah more than his overt anger."

    old "We cannot put ourselves above the rest of the country; let the troops stay in the districts."
    new "We cannot put ourselves above the rest of the country; let the troops stay in the districts."

    old "We cannot afford to weaken our defenses in the other districts, let the troops remain where they are."
    new "We cannot afford to weaken our defenses in the other districts, let the troops remain where they are."

    old "We will make do with the forces we have."
    new "We will make do with the forces we have."

    old "Marion sighed a sigh of relief."
    new "Marion sighed a sigh of relief."

    old "Thomas waived his hands."
    new "Thomas waived his hands."

    old "Each of you has your orders, you know what to do. We've spend enough time discussing these matters."
    new "Each of you has your orders, you know what to do. We've spend enough time discussing these matters."

    old "You're all dismissed."
    new "You're all dismissed."

    old "Sarah watched as one by one, each of the advisors left. She caught Varga waving at her as he left."
    new "Sarah watched as one by one, each of the advisors left. She caught Varga waving at her as he left."

    old "Then, Sarah and Thomas found themselves alone in the council room."
    new "Then, Sarah and Thomas found themselves alone in the council room."

    old "Thomas seemed to sink back into his seat, his shoulders sagging."
    new "Thomas seemed to sink back into his seat, his shoulders sagging."

    old "Sarah put her arms around him, and she began to feel his body shake, as he cried without making a sound."
    new "Sarah put her arms around him, and she began to feel his body shake, as he cried without making a sound."

    old "Even now, he puts on a front for me, she thought."
    new "Even now, he puts on a front for me, she thought."

    old "Sarah...if I mess this up..."
    new "Sarah...if I mess this up..."

    old "Don't talk like that, Thomas. You're a great king, and we will overcome this."
    new "Don't talk like that, Thomas. You're a great king, and we will overcome this."

    old "But what if we don't? If Hassar's army is large, larger than any seen, and they take the capital..."
    new "But what if we don't? If Hassar's army is large, larger than any seen, and they take the capital..."

    old "Gods, can you imagine what those barbarians would do to this city?"
    new "Gods, can you imagine what those barbarians would do to this city?"

    old "Sarah didn't need to imagine."
    new "Sarah didn't need to imagine."

    old "She had read enough history, and been lectured enough by her father on what happened to cities that were looted. And to the women in them."
    new "She had read enough history, and been lectured enough by her father on what happened to cities that were looted. And to the women in them."

    old "Sarah didn't want to think about that."
    new "Sarah didn't want to think about that."

    old "Thomas, now more than ever, you need to be strong. Imagining the worst will do nobody any good."
    new "Thomas, now more than ever, you need to be strong. Imagining the worst will do nobody any good."

    old "You made your decisions, now stand by them, have faith in your own rule."
    new "You made your decisions, now stand by them, have faith in your own rule."

    old "Sarah wished that she was as confident as she sounded to Thomas."
    new "Sarah wished that she was as confident as she sounded to Thomas."

    old "Thomas nodded, hugging her back."
    new "Thomas nodded, hugging her back."

    old "Sarah...please never leave me. I'd be lost without you."
    new "Sarah...please never leave me. I'd be lost without you."

    old "Never, Thomas, I'll never leave you."
    new "Never, Thomas, I'll never leave you."

    old "The two siblings continued to hug each other, as disaster drew nearer."
    new "The two siblings continued to hug each other, as disaster drew nearer."

